rdf:Description.lla:note: Log Book: Wednesday 23 October, Santos: Robert Smith on shore and can't be found. Thursday 24 October, Santos: Robert Smith still absent and without leave, now I write him deserted.

Log Book: Monday 21 October, Santos: John Stewart came and demands his discharge and I went with him to the Consul but the Consul refused and he was ordered back on board. Tuesday 22 October: John Stewart absent without leave…I now write him deserted.
Leghorn was English word for Livorno, Italy. Date of joining odd, should probably read 1874 as voyage did not start until October 1873
